11/03/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Thessaloniki Mayor Yiannis Boutaris announced on Thursday (March 10th) that procedures have been launched to allow the building of a mosque and a cemetery for Muslims in the city. His statement followed a meeting with Turkish Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu who was wrapping up a private visit to Greece. Davutoglu thanked Boutaris for his "sensitivity". There are currently no official religious sites for Muslims in Thessaloniki despite their growing number. (Kathimerini, Ethnos, Eleftherotypia - 11/03/11; Hurriyet - 10/03/11)
